The paper deals with learning Rectified Linear Units (ReLUs) in a reliable and efficient manner, which is a central problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary category of the paper. The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT), convex programming (cs.DS), neural networks (cs.NE), and signal processing (cs.SI), which are all relevant to the problem of learning ReLUs.
